{{- /*
DH project secrets bundle for ~/.config/dh/secrets.env, consumed by
D:/dh/mise.toml via `_.file = "~/.config/dh/secrets.env"`. mise reads
this once per shell load — solving the original "auth on every cd"
problem (mise's exec() was re-running op/cat on every directory change).

Resolved once via batched `op inject` in .chezmoi.toml.tmpl, then reused
from `.secrets.*` here.

Refresh after rotating any of these in 1Password:
    chezmoi apply --init

`private_` prefix → 0600 on Unix; no-op on Windows ACLs.

Add more dh-project-scoped env vars below as you need them. Keep them
narrow: only secrets you want available whenever you `cd D:\dh\*`.

Defensive lookup via sprig's `dig`: returns "" if `.secrets` or any
requested key is missing (e.g. remote machines bootstrapped without `op`,
or machines whose ~/.config/chezmoi/chezmoi.toml was generated before
[data.secrets] existed and hasn't been re-init'd). When the rendered
file is empty, chezmoi skips creating ~/.config/dh/secrets.env and mise
falls back gracefully (mise warns once, doesn't error).
*/ -}}
{{- $dh_pat := dig "secrets" "dh_gitlab_pat" "" . -}}
{{- $dh_clickup := dig "secrets" "dh_clickup_api_key" "" . -}}
{{- if $dh_pat }}
DH_GITLAB_TOKEN={{ $dh_pat }}
{{- end }}
{{- if $dh_clickup }}
DH_CLICKUP_API_KEY={{ $dh_clickup }}
{{- end }}
